5: Alk! Let's go on a trip!
9:
I figured it out. In order for me to get
on top, I need to go on a trip!
12:
So stop whatever you're doing and
let's head out!
25:
Ahh! So this is what a pioneer village
looks like, huh?
33:
...I can at least show you around. But
does going on a trip have to do with
becoming a top-ranker?
37:
You see, I'm out here to search for
something that I lack.
44:
Not quite. What I'm lacking is
"myself".
48:
How do I put it... I need to
understand life itself more deeply?
Or maybe it's that I lack a solid
sense of self-confidence?
52:
I have to understand myself if I'm
going to become number one in the
ring. That's what I'm out here for!
55:
So you're hoping to find... "yourself"
scattered around the village?
59:
It's a journey of self-discovery! And I
couldn't pass up the chance to see
another world. It could open my
eyes to new things, you know?
61:
Besides, it wouldn't be any fun if I
didn't have any cool stories to tell
my friends when I go back home!
65: ...So anyway, let's go talk to people!
71:
Oh, no... This guy's just really into
armor. He wears it everywhere.
75:
Hey, I'm Techtus! And that's Nimbus!
Nice to meet you, Gramps!
78:
My, you're a chipper one. I'd love to
welcome you properly... But, you see,
our village is strapped for resources
at the moment.
83:
Well... We're sort of lacking in
everything. Honestly, I'm not even
sure where to start.
86:
Huh... So your farmland's been
neglected due to a lack of
manpower?
90:
You just need to... plow? Plow the
field here, right? What's the problem?
93:
He just told us. Not enough folk to till
the land.
97: You could just use a tractor
101:
Ah! You don't have a tractor, right!
Doing this by hand would be a huge
pain, for sure!
105: All right, I'll be your tractor, then!
118:
Hahaha! This dirt doesn't stand a
chance before the might of Techtus
the Tractor!
135:
I got some sand in my joints... OW!
Was giving me pain sensors there
REALLY necessary?
139:
Hey Nimbus, is this what muscle
fatigue after a workout feels like?
148:
I'm just a useless airhead... Sorry for
trying to show off.
151:
Don't worry about it. We'll be able to
get a lot of use out of the land you
prepared for us, and that's more
than enough.
153:
There's no sense in always
overdoing it. We have to do our best
with what we have, steadily making
what progress we're able to.
155:
Obstacles will surely come, but it's
best to take them one day at a time.
A new day brings new solutions.
157:
That's a great attitude to have.
Right, Techtus
170:
What a strong-willed outlook on life!
That's exactly what I need! What an
admirable man...
173:
Take it easy... Think too hard about
this stuff and you're bound to fall for
someone's sketchy pitch again.
178:
I-I'm thinking carefully, don't worry! I
used to work in construction, you
know? Preparing farmland like that
is tough work!
181:
It's easy to talk about making steady
progress every day, but it's a hard
thing to actually pull off.
184:
That old man talked about it so
matter-of-factly, but it's amazing
that he has that outlook given the
obstacles they face every day!
188:
So I wanted to do what I could to
help...
192:
And that's where Techtus the Tractor
was born...
196:
Heh-heh... You can just forget about
that one, okay? It was... lame as hell...
200: Haha. I thought it suited you.
205:
If I'm going to be number one in the
ring, I've gotta be quick on my feet
with solving problems!
208:
I guess that's also something that
only comes from steady, everyday
growth...
212:
Wow... That whole trip was a great
learning experience.
227:
...Dunno. But my outlook on life
changed! Total change of heart!
230:
So just like that man... I'm going to
do the best every day with what I
have!
237:
Alk! Nimbus! Let's make a band!
Being in a band is exactly what I
need!
